Skottie: Sketching using Boogie

This tool is a fork starting from:
    Boogie v54898
    SpecSharp v54900


BUILD INSTRUCTIONS
------------------

A. Builld SscSharp [* Run as Admin ]

   cd $SKOTTIE\SpecSharp\SpecSharp\Microsoft.SpecSharp\LastKnownGood9
   clean.cmd
   RegisterLKG.cmd

   cd $SKOTTIE\SpecSharp\SpecSharp
   devenv SpecSharp.sln /build DebugCommandLine
   devenv SpecSharp.sln /build Debug

B. Build Boogie/SscBoogie

   cd $SKOTTIE\Boogie\Binaries
   nmake
   cd ..\Source
   devenv Boogie.sln /build Debug
   cd ..\..\SpecSharp\SscBoogie\Binaries
   nmake
   cd ..\Source
   devenv SscBoogie.sln /build Debug
   cd ..\Binaries
   nmake register

COMPILING INSTRUCTIONS
----------------------

$SKOTTIE\Boogie\Binaries\ssc.exe /debug+ <FILENAME>.ssc

    * Notes: 
      
        /debug+ is required!

SKETCHING INSTRUCTIONS
----------------------

$SKOTTIE\SpecSharp\SscBoogie\Binaries\SscBoogie.exe /sketch <Options> <FILENAME>.exe

    * Notes: 
      
        /sketch is required!
        
        [Inline] attribute enabled on method decls

    * Options:

        /proverLog:C:\Temp\z3-@PROC@

            store Z3 call logs for various sketching steps for debugging
        
        /traceSketch

            print sketching related debug info
    
        /numCEGARItrs:N        

            MAX number of CEGAR based synthesis iterations (default = 20)

        /numRandInpGen:N       

            number of random tuples for CEGAR synthesis (default = 20)

        /numThreads:N

            runs Parallel Z3 with N threads (default = 0)

	/unboundRandInpArrLen

            do not impose implicit array length bound (= 10) when generating random arrays as input

